forum on careers in philanthropy and non profits forum on careers in philanthropy and non profits moderated by hewlett foundation president paul brest this panel discussion will address career placement in the non profit and philanthropic sectors for undergraduate and graduate students panelists include barry newstead from bridgespan group ivan barkhorn from redstone strategy company and smita singh from the hewlett foundation representatives from bay area non profits government agencies and stanford university will be available to discuss career opportunities beginning at 3 30pm in kresge lobby date and time monday november 17 2008 4 00 pm approximate duration of 1.5 hour s location kresge auditorium map audience faculty staff students category lectures readings sponsor public policy program and stanford institute for economic policy research contact 736 2319 nikic stanford edu download add to personal calendar vcal record email event print use this permalink last modified november 6 2008
